Sentencas: A metal-supported solid oxide fuel cell design offers competitive advantages, for example reduced material costs and improved robustness.
Titulo: Manufacturing and characterization of metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: This paper reports the performance and stability of a recently developed metal-supported cell design, based on a novel cermet anode, on a 25 cm(2) (1 cm(2)/16 cm(2) active area) cell level.
Titulo: Manufacturing and characterization of metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: An electrochemical performance comparable to state-of-the-art anode-supported cells is demonstrated.
Titulo: Manufacturing and characterization of metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Detailed electrochemical analysis allowed assignment of the overall polarization losses quantitatively to gas diffusion in the metal support, electrooxidation in the anode functional layer, oxygen reduction in the mixed ionic-electronic conducting cathode and an additional polarization process with a rather high relaxation frequency, which may be assigned to an insulating corrosion interlayer.
Titulo: Manufacturing and characterization of metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The durability of the cells was investigated by means of galvanostatic operation for periods of up to 1000 h as well as the dynamic behavior, such as redox-, load- and thermal cycling tests.
Titulo: Manufacturing and characterization of metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The galvanostatic stability tests indicated a fair, but significant degradation rate (similar to 5% decrease in cell voltage/1000 h at 650 degrees C and 0.25 A cm(-2)).
Titulo: Manufacturing and characterization of metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Furthermore, the metal-supported cells underwent an endurance test of 100 redox cycles at 800 degrees C without severe degradation nor total failure.
Titulo: Manufacturing and characterization of metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells
